---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import onlineEnrolImage from "../../../images/future-state/online-enrol.png";
import onlinePaymentAndDigitalCardsImage from "../../../images/future-state/Online payment & digital cards.png";
import prototypeEnrolmentDetailImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/Enrolement screen - detail.png";
import prototypeMyGroupGpsImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/MyGroup - GPS.png";
import prototypeMyGroupPaymentsImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/MyGroup - Payments.png";
import prototypeMyGroupEmotionImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/MyGroup - emotion.png";
import prototypeMyGroupHomeImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/MyGroup Home.png";
import prototypeMyGroupQrImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/MyGroup QR.png";
import prototypeNotificationEnrolmentImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/Notification - new enrolment.png";
import prototypeNotificationFirstWeighImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/Notification - first weigh.png";
import prototypePosAlternativeImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/POS - alternative-3.png";
import prototypeWhatToExpectImage from "../../../images/future-state/prototypes/what to expect - new.png";
import ppt004Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.004.png";
import ppt005Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.005.png";
import ppt006Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.006.png";
import ppt008Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.008.png";
import ppt009Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.009.png";
import ppt011Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.011.png";
import ppt013Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.013.png";
import ppt015Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.015.png";
import ppt018Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.018.png";
import ppt021Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.021.png";
import ppt026Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.026.png";
import ppt029Image from "../../../images/future-state/PPT/XpressWeigh-vision.029.png";
---

<BaseLayout title="Future State · Case Study">
  <section>
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/home">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span aria-current="page">Future State</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="hero-title">
      Journey mapping as a tool to bring clarity to ambiguity<span
        class="flourish-period">.</span
      >
    </h1>

    <ul class="meta-list meta-list--casestudy meta-list--pills">
      <li></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="hero-wrapper">
      <section class="hero-lead">
        <p>
          <strong>
            I used future-state journey mapping to model how members,
            Consultants and systems interact across critical touchpoints, bringing
            systems thinking into early transformation discussions.
          </strong>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card card--role card--compact card--transparent">
        <h2>Role</h2>
        <ul class="role-list">
          <li>Cross-functional collaboration</li>
          <li>Future-state modelling</li>
          <li>Interaction design & narrative development</li>
          <li>Journey mapping & service blueprinting</li>

          <li>Executive-level presentation & alignment</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>

    <ul class="tools-list"></ul>
    <h1 class="phase-title"><span>Prologue</span></h1>
<div style="padding:0 48px; font-style:italic;">    <p>
      Around 18 months before organisation-wide transformation was announced, I
      worked with a product owner and business analyst to develop a set of
      future-state service blueprints exploring what joined-up systems thinking
      could look like from a user perspective.
    </p><p>
      Using those blueprints, I built a narrative that clarified how connected
      systems might reshape the critical early interactions between members and
      consultants. I presented that vision to the Managing Director.
    </p>
    </div>

    <span class="phase-title"></span>
    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>Problem</h2>

      <p>
        Once transformation was announced, there was broad agreement that
        systems needed to become more connected, but little clarity on what that
        meant in practice.
      </p>

      <p>
        Ideas such as digital membership cards, online enrolment and online
        payments were already in discussion, alongside a push for greater member
        self-service.
      </p>

      <p>
        Individually, these proposals made sense. What was missing was a shared
        view of how they would combine into joined-up journeys between members
        and Consultants — and how those journeys would feel across channels.
      </p>

      <p>
        Without modelling that end to end, there was a risk of improving
        isolated touchpoints while leaving the overall experience fragmented.
      </p>
    </section>
    <div class="image-row image-row--full image-row--6">
      <Image src={ppt004Image} alt="Future state vision slide 1" />
      <Image src={ppt005Image} alt="Future state vision slide 2" />
      <Image src={ppt006Image} alt="Future state vision slide 3" />
      <Image src={ppt008Image} alt="Future state vision slide 4" />
      <Image src={ppt009Image} alt="Future state vision slide 5" />
      <Image src={ppt011Image} alt="Future state vision slide 6" />
    </div>
    <div class="image-row image-row--full image-row--6">
      <Image src={ppt013Image} alt="Future state vision slide 7" />
      <Image src={ppt015Image} alt="Future state vision slide 8" />
      <Image src={ppt018Image} alt="Future state vision slide 9" />
      <Image src={ppt021Image} alt="Future state vision slide 10" />
      <Image src={ppt026Image} alt="Future state vision slide 11" />
      <Image src={ppt029Image} alt="Future state vision slide 12" />
    </div>
    <p class="image-row--caption">
      Long before transformation began, I had mapped and presented one vision of
      the future to the then Managing Director. <em
        >A selection of slides shown.</em
      >
    </p>
    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>Sign-up journey</h2>

      <p>
        Building on my earlier vision work, I began by modelling online
        enrolment as a standalone journey.
      </p>

      <p>
        Moving enrolment online appears straightforward, but in this context it
        changes when and how the relationship between member and Consultant
        begins. By mapping both actors across channels and time, I was able to
        pinpoint the moments that shape those early interactions.
      </p>

      <p>
        Mapping enrolment also surfaced a structural tension within the
        franchise model. If a potential member selects a specific group and then
        does not attend, who is the data controller under GDPR? At what point
        does responsibility sit with the franchisee, and when does it revert to
        the central organisation?
      </p>

      <p>The map did not resolve these questions. <strong>It made them visible.</strong></p>
    </section>

    <section class="image-row image-row--full-bleed">
      <p class="image-overlay">Tap to view full map</p>
      <button
        class="lightbox-trigger"
        type="button"
        data-lightbox-target="online-enrol-map"
        aria-label="Open online enrolment map full size"
      >
        <Image
          src={onlineEnrolImage}
          alt="Online enrolment journey map"
          widths={[480, 768, 1024, 1440, 1920]}
          sizes="200vw"
        />
      </button>
    </section>
    <dialog
      class="lightbox"
      data-lightbox="online-enrol-map"
      aria-label="Online enrolment map"
    >
      <div class="lightbox__actions">
        <button class="lightbox__toggle" type="button" aria-pressed="false">
          Fit height
        </button>
        <button class="lightbox__close" type="button" aria-label="Close">
          ×
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="lightbox__inner">
        <div class="lightbox__image">
          <img
            src={onlineEnrolImage.src}
            alt="Online enrolment journey map"
            draggable="false"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </dialog>
    <p class="image-row--caption">
      Online enrolment map used to model the end-to-end member sign-up journey.
      The original map was built in Figma and featured embedded interactive
      prototypes.
    </p>

    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>
        Payments and verification journey
      </h2>

      <p>
        At the time, payment and membership verification operated through a
        hybrid mix of analogue and digital processes that lacked cohesion.
        Consultants managed attendance and payments within live sessions, with
        limited system visibility.
      </p>

      <p>
        I modelled how online payments and membership verification could
        function within that environment without undermining the live group
        dynamic.
      </p>

      <h3>Online payments</h3>

      <p>
        Online payments were widely regarded as a priority, but the franchise
        structure introduced structural constraints.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          As a franchiser, Slimming World cannot directly accept and hold
          payments on behalf of franchisees.
        </li>
        <li>
          Members can attend any group nationally without pre-booking, and
          consultants are legally able to set their own pricing.   This means the concept of purchasing a fixed “attendance” did not
        translate cleanly into a digital journey. 
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
      I explored a wallet-style
        top-up and charge-at-point-of-use model, supported by an escrow
        structure aligned with franchise and financial boundaries.
      </p>

<h3>Digital member card</h3>

<p>
The digital member card was treated as a portable identity layer. Members are able to attend any group nationally, so verification needed to travel with them — clearly representing membership status across locations and functioning reliably when connectivity was inconsistent.
</p>

<p>
I developed a proof-of-concept QR-based card to demonstrate how essential member data could travel with the individual, enabling verification without reliance on a live lookup.
</p>

      <h3>Member app integration</h3>

      <p>
        Separate from verification, I explored ways the member app could become
        part of the joined-up group experience rather than a parallel digital
        channel. The map modelled app-supported moments within the live session,
        alongside self-serve behaviours such as absence booking and balance
        visibility.
      </p>

      <p>
        The intent was to reduce administrative friction while reinforcing — not
        replacing — the central role of the Consultant in the group setting.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="image-row image-row--full-bleed">
      <p class="image-overlay">Tap to view full map</p>
      <button
        class="lightbox-trigger"
        type="button"
        data-lightbox-target="online-payment-map"
        aria-label="Open online payment and digital cards map full size"
      >
        <Image
          src={onlinePaymentAndDigitalCardsImage}
          alt="Online payment and digital cards journey map"
          widths={[480, 768, 1024, 1440, 1920]}
          sizes="200vw"
        />
      </button>
    </section>

    <dialog
      class="lightbox"
      data-lightbox="online-payment-map"
      aria-label="Online payment and digital cards map"
    >
      <div class="lightbox__actions">
        <button class="lightbox__toggle" type="button" aria-pressed="false">
          Fit height
        </button>
        <button class="lightbox__close" type="button" aria-label="Close">
          ×
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="lightbox__inner">
        <div class="lightbox__image">
          <img
            src={onlinePaymentAndDigitalCardsImage.src}
            alt="Online payment and digital cards journey map"
            draggable="false"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </dialog>
    <p class="image-row--caption">
Multi-actor journey map showing how members, consultants and systems connect across payments, verification and app-enhanced group interactions.
    </p>
    <div class="image-row image-row--full image-row--2">
      <Image src={prototypeEnrolmentDetailImage} alt="Prototype enrolment detail screen" />
      <Image src={prototypePosAlternativeImage} alt="Prototype POS alternative screen" />
    </div>
    <div class="image-row image-row--full image-row--4">
        <Image src={prototypeMyGroupPaymentsImage} alt="Prototype MyGroup payments screen" />
       <Image src={prototypeMyGroupQrImage} alt="Prototype MyGroup QR screen" />
      <Image src={prototypeMyGroupGpsImage} alt="Prototype MyGroup GPS screen" />
      <Image src={prototypeMyGroupHomeImage} alt="Prototype MyGroup home screen" />
        
    </div>
    <div class="image-row image-row--full image-row--4">
       <Image src={prototypeWhatToExpectImage} alt="Prototype what to expect screen" />
        <Image src={prototypeMyGroupEmotionImage} alt="Prototype MyGroup emotion screen" />
      <Image src={prototypeNotificationEnrolmentImage} alt="Prototype new enrolment notification screen" />
      <Image src={prototypeNotificationFirstWeighImage} alt="Prototype first weigh notification screen" />
    </div>
    <p class="image-row--caption">
A number of existing and new prototypes brought the maps to life with interactivity.

    </p>
    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>Impact</h2>

      <p><strong>
        These maps were not intended to resolve every question. Their purpose
        was to surface the right ones and make abstract ideas tangible.
      </strong></p>

      <p>
        By modelling joined-up journeys across actors and touchpoints, I gave
        structure to concepts that had previously been discussed in isolation.
        Assumptions became visible, trade-offs clearer, and dependencies easier
        to understand.
      </p>

      <p>
        The artefacts provided a practical reference point for deeper analysis
        as the programme progressed, helping shift discussion from individual
        features to how the service would need to work in reality.
      </p>
    </section>

  </section>
</BaseLayout>
<script type="module" src="/scripts/lightbox.js"></script>
